<TEXT>
a month after the 60th academy awards evidence 
persists that the oscars golden touch doesnt always live up to 
its reputation 
columbia pictures had hoped that the sweep of nine oscars by 
the last emperor would result in a boxoffice bonanza but 
despite doubling the number of theaters to more than 800 after the 
awards the chinese epic has added only 10 million to theater 
grosses 
after 164 days in release the last emperor had sold 366 
million worth of tickets in the united states and canada by 
comparison the ghostly comedy beetlejuice grossed 467 
million in just 33 days 
still james r spitz president of columbias domestic 
distribution maintains the last emperor has had a very good 
performance since the awards 
comparing the last emperor to beetlejuice is like 
comparing apples to oranges he said the last emperor will 
never have the teenage audience that beetlejuice has 
spitz predicted the bernardo bertolucci film will continue doing 
good business through memorial day and will remain in distribution 
for a long time 
moonstruck which collected acting awards for cher and 
olympia dukakis has added 10 million since the oscars bringing 
its total to 69 million the figure is impressive since the film 
had been in wide release for more than two months 
much has been written about how winning oscars can inflate 
actors salaries with one exception this years winners seem 
unlikely to boost their paychecks 
since romancing the stone and fatal attraction michael 
douglas has become one of the most indemand stars in hollywood 
his win for wall street will have little effect on douglas who 
sometimes produces his own films the china syndrome jewel 
of the nile 
douglas next film is for sherry lansing and stanley jaffe who 
produced fatal attraction in black rain he will play an 
american police officer trying to solve a murder by the yakusa the 
japanese mafia 
having appeared in the witches of eastwick suspect and 
moonstruck in 1987 cher can afford a rest no new films have 
been announced for her in the wake of the oscar but the scripts 
must be piling up at her door meanwhile she will collect a 
fortune with her las vegas act 
sean connery winner as supporting actor in the 
untouchables needs no help from oscar or anyone else in his 
career he has been a top wage earner since his james bond days 
hell appear this summer in presidio with mark harmon and 
works next as harrison fords father in the third indiana jones 
movie 
olympia dukakis seems to be the major recipient of oscars 
beneficence although a distinguished stage actress she was little 
known before moonstruck since her nomination she has been 
able to decline two offers for television series she has accepted 
a small role in mike nichols working girls which stars 
melanie griffith harrison ford and sigourney weaver but her 
agents predict big things for her 
the april 11 oscar show drew generally poor notices but also the 
best television rating in years 
the ratings show that we didnt lose our audience even during 
a sweep by the last emperor said samuel goldwyn jr who 
produced the show for the academy i tried to prevent that by 
putting a heavy load of comedy robin williams eddie murphy 
toward the end the audience stayed with us 
goldwyn recognized the problems in moving to the shrine 
auditorium with its poor acoustics and the horendous traffic jam 
but those problems can be solved i think we benefited from 
having 6000 in the theater it was a much warmer audience the 
music center where the awards show previously was staged held 
only 2000 people 
most critics lambasted the 3hour broadcast time and goldwyn 
commented that the academy will have to address that problem 
there are certain things in the show that the academy is 
interested in but the public isnt he said 
efforts to eliminate such awards as short subjects 
documentaries and animation from the show have so far failed to 
achieve board of governors approval 
will goldwyn be around next year to help deal with such problems 
not on your life he said two years is enough 
