sharp right turn hit a utility pole overturned and came to rest 
on its side about 30 feet from the road and just a few feet from 
little wappingers creek state police sgt dennis cody said 
it was not immediately known what caused the accident cody said 
witnesses described the wreckage as looking like a crushed 
yellow school bus the safety of converted school buses is under 
scrutiny this week after a fiery weekend crash in kentucky killed 
at least 27 people on a church outing the passengers who were 
