the federal government plans to make federal 
transit subsidies contingent on local drug testing programs for 
city transit bus and subway operators 
alfred dellibovi head of the urban mass transit administration 
said monday that new regulations would require operators to submit 
to a broad range of drug tests including random sampling 
the federal regulations will call on transit officials to test 
for illegal use of drugs before employment after an accident for 
reasonable cause and under a random selection process according to 
dellibovi 
operators of buses and subway trains as well as others in 
sensitive jobs such as train dispatchers would be subject to 
the testing he said 
umta provides federal financial assistance to transit systems 
although a testing program would have to be imposed and 
administered by the local transit authorities 
