cutbacks brought on by budget cuts have 
lowered the price tag on the major weapons programs central to 
president reagans military buildup by 618 billion 
the pentagon said monday that at the close of the quarter on 
dec 31 the 95 key programs carried a combined price tag of 
75725 billion down 75 percent from the adjusted sept 30 1987 
total of 81905 billion 
the pentagon attributed the quarterly decline to seven programs 
that were either cancelled or significantly cut back in order 
to comply with fiscal 1988 spending limits adopted last fall in a 
compromise deficitreduction package 
among the seven were production of copperhead artillery rounds 
development and production of surveillance drone aircraft and 
development of a jamproof high frequency radio system those cuts 
respectively saved 4233 million 13 billion and 44 billion 
also killed were the groundlaunched cruise missile program and 
the satellitekilling asat rocket 
