that he and shultz had devoted their entire talk to the kremlins 
position 
peres said he had told the soviets at meetings last week in 
spain and in hungary that they have to do more and in a more 
determined fashion to boost the flagging peace initiative 
i told them that their fear of the arab reaction is 
exaggerated because the arabs need peace talks no less than we 
do he said the soviets have expressed concern privately that 
their radical arab allies might be angry if they joined the peace 
process 
syria a close ally of moscows rejects the shultz plan but the 
more moderate jordan has said it welcomes soviet participation 
