<TEXT>
israel set up emergency telephone hotlines 
tuesday and readied insecticidespraying airplanes to fly into 
action against a possible plague of locusts the desert insects 
feared since biblical times 
only a small number of the yellow insects were sighted in 
southern israel and the jordan valley but officials warned of a 
possible larger invasion from the south and said the hotlines would 
remain open until the end of the week at least 
if they are not controlled locusts can destroy all the 
countrys crops and orchards in a matter of days said chaim 
hahan an agriculture ministry official working on the hotline 
if the winds are right they can travel about 130 miles per 
day he said they are fast and deadly 
locust migrations occur infrequently after a buildup of the 
population swarms of the insects can obscure the sun when they 
pass overhead and turn the ground black when they settle to rest 
for the night 
some crops are destroyed by the flying swarm but most of the 
destruction occurs after the insects lay eggs at night the larvae 
which hatch in 15 to 20 days devour all green vegetation 
the last serious locust invasion into israel was in 1959 then 
israel was younger and less modernized and many israelis banged 
pots and pans outdoors in an attempt to scare off the swarms 
hahan said it didnt work 
but this year israel is ready with planes and has asked 
residents to call the hotline if they spot insect swarms covering 
up to four to five acres which officials fear could come from 
egypts sinai desert where some have been seen 
it takes a swarm of 5000 to 10000 insects before we get 
really worried hahan said and even if a farmer sees that 
many he shouldnt take any action on his own wait for us 
israels concern was heightened by a fourday heat wave the 
worst in the country in 18 years warm weather is one environmental 
factor known to trigger locust migration 
due to hot winds from the north temperatures in parts of israel 
and the occupied west bank have reached 113 degrees this week one 
austrian tourist died after hiking in the area of the dead sea and 
suffering from heat stroke 
