customs officials seized 136 vehicles and 
arrested 82 people mostly americans returning from canada in the 
first 40 days of the zero tolerance drug crackdown a spokesman 
said 
some of them cant believe that youre actually going to seize 
their vehicle and place them under arrest mike jordan customs 
inspector in detroit said monday to them its always just been 
just another trip over a bridge 
previously when inspectors found small amounts of a drug the 
suspect was fined up to 600 and allowed to drive away under the 
zero tolerance program inspectors automatically seize vehicles if 
any quantity of a drug is found 
the vehicles were seized in the detroit district including the 
sault ste marie and port huron areas he said 
nationally 27 boats and 700 vehicles have been seized since 
april 11 officials said 
the program received national attention with recent seizures of 
the yachts monkey business and ark royal after small amounts of 
marijuana were found on them monkey business is the charter yacht 
that once ferried presidential contender gary hart and model donna 
rice 
