the european space agency on 
tuesday launched its 22nd ariane rocket putting into orbit a 
communications satellite 
officials at the space center on the northeastern shoulder of 
south america called the launch a complete success 
the countdown had been stopped for 15 minutes at 837 pm 
because of bad weather conditions 
a storm cloud passed over the launching pad a space agency 
official said the countdown was resumed at 852 pm and the 
rocket lifted off at 858 pm 
sixteen minutes and 40 seconds later the international 
telecommunications organization satellite separated from the 
rocket according to the official 
the agency said the flight was nominal or perfect except 
for the brief weather problem 
new french premier michel rocard watched the operation from the 
space agencys facility in suburban paris 
four of the previous 21 ariane shots were unsuccessful a 
failure in 1986 grounded the program for more than a year but the 
last three launches have been a success including the previous one 
on march 12 
the intelsat vf13 satellite put into geostationary orbit 22500 
miles above the earth is part of a series of 15 satellites built by 
an international consortium headed by ford aerospace the satellite 
contains 15000 telephone circuits and two television channels 
tuesdays launch involved an ariane 2 rocket 
