<TEXT>
the secret of the spoleto festivals success is 
that there is no real program says composer gian carlo menotti 
who has led the arts celebration for three decades 
we do whatever we feel like doing we surprise our audience 
and the press he said 
we are against all commemorations during the anniversary of 
bachs birth we do beethoven during the anniversary of beethoven 
we do stravinsky we keep away from everything that is somewhat 
dictated we use instinct and imagination we dont announce a 
program two or three years in advance because we never know what 
were going to do 
this year at the 112event spoleto festival usa in 
charleston sc menotti felt like presenting dvoraks 1901 opera 
rusalka since the first act is supposed to take place under 
water rusalka has only been done in this country a handful of 
times since its american premiere in 1935 
john paull iii technical production manager for broadways 
the phantom of the opera is in charge of rusalka he is 
swathing the stage in chinablue silk for the water and bringing 
soprano maria spacagna as the water nymph rusalka who lives in 
the lake onto the stage through a trap door 
her father the water sprite at one point becomes angry and 
creates a whirlpool the silk spins round and round 
menotti founded the festival of the two worlds in spoleto 
italy in 1958 and later founded the spoleto festival usa in 
charleston this year it runs from may 20 to june 5 and the 
spoleto festival of the three worlds in melbourne australia he 
still heads all of them 
we create a festive atmosphere menotti said in a recent 
interview i always think of it involving the whole town i 
wanted to see if an artist can be as important a member of a 
community as a doctor the people of charleston have the dignity of 
knowing arts are needed 
menotti recently directed his 1950 opera the consul in 
bulgaria the opera which opened the first spoleto festival usa 
in 1977 is set in an unidentified police state in which a woman 
tries to get a visa for another country where her husband has found 
refuge 
i never thought i would ever see the consul in bulgaria 
he said i think they feel it is about some other country i had 
no trouble i asked somebody if the translation was faithful and 
the answer was yes the audience stood and cheered 
now the government has asked me to do a film of it in bulgaria 
in english they offered to pay for everything the whole 
production they only thing is they cannot pay foreign singers 
they have no dollars soprano mirella freni wants to sing the 
woman her husband bass nicolai ghiaurov is bulgarian theres no 
reason his character the chief of police shouldnt have an accent 
i accepted if im still alive im going to do it next 
year menotti will be 77 in july 
