bell amp howell co shareholders on tuesday 
approved a 702 million buyout led by texas financier robert m 
bass and members of bell amp howells management 
shareholder approval cleared the way for completion of the 
buyout of the skokiebased informationservices company by robert 
m bass group inc acadia partners lp of fort worth texas and 
certain bell amp howell executives including gerald e schultz 
chairman and chief executive officer 
the group will pay each stockholder 64 per share for their 
common and preferred stock bell amp howell said in a statement 
financing arrangements for the deal were consummated shortly 
after the shareholder approval the company said 
financing includes 200 in senior subordinated debt of which 
acadia partners is buying 30 million 344 million in bank 
financing 100 million equity participation in the form of cash 
and bell amp howell stock and 58 million of bell amp howells cash on 
hand 
